window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Controlling his griffin just got a whole lot harder…</b></p> <p>Landscape gardener Kieran's unruly shifter side is getting out of hand. Mowing lawns? Griffin time. Grocery shopping? Griffin in the cart. This is definitely not a good time to finally meet his fated mate… especially when she's only in town for a mandatory vacation.</p> <p>Workaholic Natasha never intended to return to her small hometown. And she's definitely not planning to stay. But between the delicious pies and the even more tempting Kieran, it's hard to remember why she ever left. Still, it would be foolish to fall for a guy who keeps disappearing… right?</p> <p>But Kieran's not the only mystery in town. Between the possibly haunted house and a definitely charming hunk, Natasha becomes torn between the life she knows or embracing the unexpected—whatever that turns out to be.</p> <p>In a town of treats, legends, and unexpected flights of fancy, can Natasha find love that truly lifts her off her feet? Unwrap the mysteries of Girdwood Springs and find your slice of romance!</p> <p>Griffins and Apple Pies <i>is a short and sweet standalone shifter romance, full of warmth and humor, and is the third in the Shifters and Sweets series. Guaranteed HEA!</i></p>"; 
